race.comment: SHISUTA BO (4) hasn't done a lot wrong and looks a good chance again. Caitlin Tootell will have her work cut out for her from the wide gate but if she can enjoy an economic run, she can be in the finish. As a rule, the powerful Lindsay Park stable must be respected when they campaign horses in SA so ITSUKUSHIMA (1) must be considered a winning chance. He's never won second-up, but the first-up run suggests he's come back well. The claim helps and he should be strong late. DOLCEMENTE (9) is another that doesn't traditionally win until deeper into the preparation but expecting some improvement here. She can run a place. ISUSPECTJEU (10) is untapped and looks well placed from the low draw with the claim.
